|WKOCommands
|WKO========================================

|YKBmail |BKB- |CKBloads your mail reader
|YKBcheckmail |BKB- |CKBchecks to see if you have mail
|YKBreadmail |BKB- |CKBputs you into the mail system (see arguments below)
|YKBclosemail |BKB- |CKBremoves your reader

|YKBmail <person> (only works if you have a mail reader loaded) |BKB-|CKB
        sends mail to another character.

|YKOUsing the |YKB"set" |YKOcommand, you can set your mud mail to be forwarded
to your internet email address.  See |YKB"help set"|YKO for more information.

The following commands are issued from the mail prompt.
|YKB(1-max_num)   |BKB-- |CKBShow that message number
|YKB.             |BKB-- |CKBShow the current message again
|YKB+             |BKB-- |CKBShow the next message
|YKB+<number>     |BKB-- |CKBShow the message <number> ahead of this one
|YKB-             |BKB-- |CKBShow the previous message
|YKB-<number>     |BKB-- |CKBShow the message <number> before this one
|YKBd <number>    |BKB-- |CKBDelete message <number> from your mail.
|YKBh             |BKB-- |CKBShow message headers
|YKBl             |BKB-- |CKBSave the current message to /log/<you>.mbox
|YKBn             |BKB-- |CKBGoto and show next message
|YKBR             |BKB-- |CKBReply to the current message's sender
|YKBr             |BKB-- |CKBReply to the current message's sender and Cc's
|YKBq             |BKB-- |CKBQuit mail
|YKBx             |BKB-- |CKBQuit mail without erasing any messages
|YKB?             |BKB-- |CKBShow this help information
